node.text:
Awarded the South African Fly Fishing Film of the Year for 2017.

Bamba Ubuyisele, which means Catch and Release in IsiZulu, is a film about Trevor Sithole in his tribal homelands, fishing the beautiful Mooi River which flows through the Thendela Village.

Trevor is an icon in the growth of South African fly fishing, he was introduced to fly fishing through a fly fishing project that was initiated to educate local people about the brown trout that reside in the higher reaches of the Mooi River in the Kamberg Valley of Kwa-Zulu Natal. Trevor was inspired by other members in the community who took initiative in the project and it was not long before he became fully involved.

Read more about the Thendela Fly Fishing Project at thendelaflyfishing.co.za/

Filming and Editing: Matt Gorlei @mattgorlei 
Cast: Trevor Sithole @flysaint1 
Location: Thendela

Music by: 
Johnny Clegg & Juluka - Inkunzi Ayihlabi Ngokumisa
Ladysmith Black Mambazo - O mmu beno mmu

**A product of The FlyBru Fly Fishing Media Collective** @flybru

A short film to celebrate the inaugural Fish and Fly Trio challenge launched by Green Adventure Slovenia in 2020. 

This fishing challenge welcomes enthusiasts of all ages and abilities to participate in a unique three-day fishing excursion, including a three-night stay and a helicopter ride over one of the greenest of European countries: Slovenia. The objective of the challenge is to catch three species – grayling, brown trout and marble trout – from three pristine rivers. @green_adventure_slovenia 

Full story in @thefieldmagazine (Jan 2020) by @marinagibsonfishing 

Film & editing credits: @sebastianlindner_foto_film and @theflyfishingnation

node.text:
It's this time of the year again. The Osenka, famous on the Ponoi for their immaculate condition, and remarkable strength, these fish are what make up the first pulse of the Fall run in August. Entering as bright and plump missiles, they largely consist of two/three-year sea wintered fish. They enter under the thick winter ice and follow through to spend the entire summer in the river, only to spawn in the following years, Autumn. These deep-bodied and hard fighting fall-run fish are accompanied by an Indian-summer setting and with a little luck, some Aurora Borealis sightseeing.⁣
⁣
At the moment (as of 9 July 2021), you can only travel to Russia if you are a citizen of USA, UK, Germany, Greece, Switzerland, Italy, Austria, Japan, Turkey, Serbia, Japan, United Saudi Emirates, Egypt, Cuba, and some other countries. If your Salmon plans have suffered due to Covid Restrictions, this might be your chance to get into one of the sought-after fall weeks.⁣
⁣
Get in touch with your booking agent or contact the guys from the Ponoi River Co.⁣
